  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations to North Carolina total $3.1B in FY2026 to date. Award activity includes 122,125 awards with an average award size of $25.3K, and obligations are down 66.9% year over year. Historical annual obligations show swings from $6.7B in FY21 to $9.3B in FY25, with FY26 at $3.1B so far. The Department of Defense leads buying agencies with $1.2B, followed by the General Services Administration at $467M and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $430M. Top vendors include GENERAL DYNAMICS INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, INC. at $173M, SDV OFFICE SYSTEMS LLC at $149M, and RESEARCH TRIANGLE INSTITUTE at $136M. Leading industries by obligations in FY2026 to date are Computer Systems Design Services at $295M, Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $235M, and Engineering Services at $196M. All figures are contract obligations; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has federal contracting trended in North Carolina?",
        "body": "Obligations in FY26 to date are $3.1B, down 66.9% year over year. Annual obligations have varied: $6.7B in FY21, $8.6B in FY22, $7B in FY23, $7.2B in FY24, and $9.3B in FY25. The current-year total is a fiscal year to date figure and not a full-year total. Average award size in FY26 to date is $25.3K across 122,125 awards."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors dominate FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The top buying agency is the Department of Defense at $1.2B, followed by the General Services Administration at $467M and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $430M. Other top buyers include the Department of Health and Human Services at $227M and the Department of Homeland Security at $223M. Largest vendors are GENERAL DYNAMICS INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, INC. at $173M, SDV OFFICE SYSTEMS LLC at $149M, and RESEARCH TRIANGLE INSTITUTE at $136M."
      }
    ]
